<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author. (Year of publication). <em>Title of report</em> (Report No. or additional information 
	about report). Place of publication: Publisher.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Smith, A. R.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2056</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of report">2055 Annual report</span></em>
	<span class="hover" title="Report No. or additional information about report">(Publication No. P3&#45;4147)</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Parramatta, Australia</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">The Turning Page Bookshop</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
When the publisher is the author, use the word &#34;Author&#34; in place of a publisher&#8217;s name.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Organisation name">The Turning Page Bookshop</span>. 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2056</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of report">2055 Annual report</span></em>
	<span class="hover" title="Report No. or additional information about report">(Publication No. P3&#45;4147)</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Parramatta, Australia</span>: Author.
</blockquote>
